    "body": "From [here](https://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/):\r\n\r\n> Many binaries depend on numpy-1.13+mkl\r\n\r\nSo I believe that projects using NumPy's C API are built against NumPy 1.13. Is that correct @cgohlke?\r\n\r\n> On the README it says \"NumPy: 1.7.0 or higher\" so this should work, right?\r\n\r\nI think it's 1.8 now (need to update the README.md), but that's if you're building from source."
